- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the study of words and their properties, which is a central topic in formal languages and automata theory.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves combinatorial and discrete structures such as words, prefixes, and special factors.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper discusses the characteristic parameters of words, which are important in information theory for data compression and coding.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the properties of words and their prefixes, which can be seen as data structures.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves the study of the complexity of words and their properties.
